Date:  10/4/1901
Source:  Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:  41
Edition:
Quote:  OLD BOY writes - Can any of your readers enlighten me as to the origin or meaning of the very common school word now used - "Bonse" or "Bonser."  Be it a large apple or a good stroke at tennis "Oh, that's a bonser!" we hear at once.  Has it anything to do with "Bonanza"?
